"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\n<span style=\"font-size:16px;\">William Stookley:</span><br />\n<span style=\"font-size:16px;\">was first a grocer by trade and then a House and Estate Agent, but also he was a Lay preacher. ( We know that he was a partaker of the holy communion at the Holy Trinity Church, Upper Tooting, London. It was thought that he preached at the Holy Trinity Church however there is a note book that is believed to belong to William Stookely which has a hand written sermon giving reference to the Upper Tooting Methodist Church. As at this date May 2019 we have no firm evidence to where William did preach.)</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
